{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Test Coverage Guardian",
  "description": "Warns when new code is added without corresponding test files, especially for middleware business logic and API endpoints",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "backend/src/**/*.ts",
      "middleware/src/**/*.ts",
      "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check if a corresponding test file exists for the newly created file. Analyze:\n1. For middleware files (unitConverter, recipeScaler, etc.): Check for both unit tests and property-based tests\n2. For backend services: Check for unit tests and integration tests\n3. For API controllers: Check for integration tests\n4. For React components: Check for component tests\n5. For utility functions: Check for unit tests\n\nIf tests are missing, provide guidance on:\n- Where to create the test file (tests/unit/, tests/integration/, tests/property/)\n- What test cases should be covered\n- Whether property-based tests are needed (for calculations)\n- Suggest test structure and key scenarios to test\n\nRemind the developer that the project requires comprehensive testing, especially for business logic."
  }
}